==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: makomako
<hw>makomako</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A graceful deciduous shrub or small
tree (<spn>Aristotelia serrata</spn>) having attractive foliage and
small red berries that turn black at maturity and are used for making
wine.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> New Zealand wine berry, wineberry, <spn>Aristotelia
serrata</spn>, <spn>Aristotelia racemosa</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>mako shark</ent>⟦br⟧
